Maintainer: Kuan Liu <kuan.liu@utoronto.ca>
Description: Implements Bayesian marginal structural models for causal effect estimation in longitudinal observational studies
             with longitudinal treatments. It includes an extension to handle informative right censoring. The Bayesian importance sampling weights are estimated using JAGS 
             and the Bayesian non-parametric bootstrap is implemented using optimation with Dirichlet sampling weights. See Saarela et al. (2015) <doi:10.1111/biom.12269> and Liu et al. (2020) <doi:10.1177/0962280219900362> for methodological details. 
